import java.io.DataOutputStream;
import java.net.Socket;

public class UDPClient {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        Socket s = new Socket("localhost", 3000);
        DataOutputStream dout = new DataOutputStream(s.getOutputStream());
        dout.writeUTF("Hello Server");
        dout.flush();
        dout.close();
        s.close();
    }
}

<<<explanation>>>:

The DataOutputStream class is a filter output stream that converts data written to the output stream into bytes. The class provides methods for writing primitive data types to the output stream.

The writeUTF(String str) method writes a string to the output stream. The string is encoded into a sequence of bytes using the modified UTF-8 encoding. The length of the string is written as a 16-bit integer.

The flush() method flushes the output stream.

The close() method closes the output stream.

The Socket class represents a socket connection to a remote host. The constructor takes the host name and the port number as arguments.

The getOutputStream() method returns an OutputStream object that can be used to write data to the socket.

